  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Major George Luther Stearns died; he was John Brown&apos;s right hand man. William Lloyd Garrison is looking forward to seeing Francis Jackson Garrison and the Villards. Mrs. Helen Eliza Garrison&apos;s leg ulcer is healing. William L. Garrison writes: &quot;Miss Wiggins leaves us to-day, after a visit of four months.&quot; Mr. and Mrs. Oliver Johnson arrived for a visit yesterday. R. W. Emerson spoke at George Luther Stearn&apos;s funeral. A temperance meeting in honor of Senator Henry Wilson was held in Tremont Temple. Garrison says: &quot;Black has taken the best photograph of me that I have had taken. I shall bring some copies with me.&quot; Billings&apos;s portrait of him is good. The National Testimonial will be presented on May 1.</subfield>
